ops.insert: When using bioelectrical impedance for measuring body composition, why does an electrical current travel faster through muscle than it does through fat?

textDelta: When using bioelectrical impedance for measuring body composition, why does an electrical current travel faster through muscle than it does through fat? The electrical current travels faster through muscle because muscle is a better conductor of electricity than fat.

When using bioelectrical impedance for measuring body composition, why does an electrical current travel faster through muscle than it does through fat? The electrical current travels faster through muscle because muscle is more electrically conductive than fat.

ops.insert: Within the United Nations, real power is located in

textDelta: Within the United Nations, real power is located in the Security Council. The Security Council is the most powerful body within the United Nations. It has the authority to make decisions that are binding on all member states. The Security Council also has the power to impose sanctions and to authorize the use of force.
